{"type":"message","id":"1655ea6d","parentId":"05d4e26d","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:15:23.277Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Investigating the API File**\n\nI've located the likely API file. I'm now examining the contents of `DMarket-Telegram-Bot-main/src/dmarket/dmarket_api.py` to confirm its suitability. This should give me the insights I need to proceed.\n\n\n"},{"type":"text","text":"I will read `DMarket-Telegram-Bot-main/src/dmarket/dmarket_api.py` to check if it contains the necessary API interaction logic.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771157723272_607","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"DMarket-Telegram-Bot-main/src/dmarket/dmarket_api.py"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":10222,"output":155,"cacheRead":8040,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":10377,"cost":{"input":0.020444,"output":0.00186,"cacheRead":0.001608,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.023912000000000003}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771157719529}}
{"type":"message","id":"a40ab08c","parentId":"1655ea6d","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:15:23.296Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771157723272_607","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"Modular DMarket API client for 2026.\n\nThis is the v2 implementation of the DMarket Client, standardized according to SACS-2026.\nIt provides a unified interface for interacting with the DMarket API.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport logging\nfrom typing import TYPE_CHECKING, Any, Dict, List, Optional\n\nfrom src.dmarket.api.client import GAME_MAP, BaseDMarketClient, api_cache\nfrom src.dmarket.api.extended import ExtendedMixin\nfrom src.dmarket.api.inventory import InventoryMixin\nfrom src.dmarket.api.market import MarketMixin\nfrom src.dmarket.api.trading import TradingMixin\nfrom src.dmarket.api.wallet import WalletMixin\n\nif TYPE_CHECKING:\n    pass\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\n\nclass DMarketAPI(\n    BaseDMarketClient,\n    MarketMixin,\n    WalletMixin,\n    TradingMixin,\n    InventoryMixin,\n    ExtendedMixin,\n):\n    \"\"\"Facade for DMarket API v2.0.0 (SACS-2026 standardized).\"\"\"\n\n    VERSION = \"2.0.0\"\n\n    async def direct_balance_request(self) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Direct balance request logic (v2 implementation).\"\"\"\n        logger.info(\"Executing direct balance request (v2)\")\n        return await self._request(\"GET\", \"/account/v1/balance\")\n\n    async def get_user_targets(\n        self,\n        game_id: str,\n        status: Optional[str] = None,\n        limit: int = 100,\n        offset: int = 0,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Retrieve user targets with standardized filtering.\"\"\"\n        mapped_game_id = GAME_MAP.get(game_id.lower(), game_id)\n        params = {\n            \"GameID\": mapped_game_id,\n            \"Limit\": str(limit),\n            \"Offset\": str(offset),\n        }\n        if status:\n            params[\"BasicFilters.Status\"] = status\n            \n        logger.debug(f\"Fetching user targets for game {mapped_game_id}\")\n        return await self._request(\n            \"GET\", \"/marketplace-api/v1/user-targets\", params=params\n        )\n\n    async def get_sacs_compliance_status(self) -> Dict[str, str]:\n        \"\"\"Check compliance with SACS-2026 standards.\"\"\"\n        return {\n            \"status\": \"compliant\",\n            \"version\": self.VERSION,\n            \"standard\": \"SACS-2026\"\n        }\n\n    async def clear_cache(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Clear the API cache.\"\"\"\n        api_cache.clear()\n        logger.info(\"API cache cleared (v2)\")\n\n    async def clear_cache_for_endpoint(self, endpoint_path: str) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Clear specific cache entries.\"\"\"\n        keys_to_remove = [k for k in api_cache if endpoint_path in k]\n        for k in keys_to_remove:\n            api_cache.pop(k, None)\n        logger.info(\n            f\"Cleared {len(keys_to_remove)} cache entries for {endpoint_path} (v2)\"\n        )\n\n    async def __aenter__(self) -> \"DMarketAPI\":\n        \"\"\"Async context manager entry.\"\"\"\n        async with self._client_lock:\n            self._client_ref_count += 1\n            await self._get_client()\n        return self\n\n    async def __aexit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Async context manager exit.\"\"\"\n        async with self._client_lock:\n            self._client_ref_count -= 1\n            if self._client_ref_count <= 0:\n                await self._close_client()\n                self._client_ref_count = 0\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771157723294}}
{"type":"message","id":"b8a31dc4","parentId":"a40ab08c","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:15:28.558Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Examining the Inheritance**\n\nI'm focused on the inheritance structure of `DMarketAPI`. It's clear that `MarketMixin` contains the core market operations, specifically price fetching, while `DMarketAPI` utilizes these methods. I'm now examining the import structure to better understand how `src.dmarket.api.market` is integrated.\n\n\n**Investigating File Paths**\n\nI'm now tracing the file paths to pinpoint the location of `src/dmarket/api/market.py`, so I can see how `MarketMixin` and its methods, particularly price fetching, are defined and used. This should clarify how the API handles market data.\n\n\n"},{"type":"text","text":"I will read `DMarket-Telegram-Bot-main/src/dmarket/api/market.py` to find the functions for fetching market prices and item details.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771157728553_609","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"DMarket-Telegram-Bot-main/src/dmarket/api/market.py"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":11251,"output":138,"cacheRead":8275,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":11389,"cost":{"input":0.022501999999999998,"output":0.0016560000000000001,"cacheRead":0.0016550000000000002,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.025813}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771157723296}}
{"type":"message","id":"9bce4cb0","parentId":"b8a31dc4","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:15:28.576Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771157728553_609","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"๏ปฟ\"\"\"Market operations for DMarket API.\"\"\"\r\n\r\nfrom typing import Any\r\n\r\nfrom src.dmarket.api.client import GAME_MAP\r\nfrom src.dmarket.api_validator import validate_response\r\nfrom src.dmarket.schemas import MarketItemsResponse  # Updated v2.0 schema  # Updated v2.0 schema\r\n\r\n\r\nclass MarketMixin:\r\n    \"\"\"Methods for interacting with DMarket marketplace.\"\"\"\r\n\r\n    @validate_response(MarketItemsResponse, endpoint=\"/exchange/v1/market/items\")\r\n    async def get_market_items(\r\n        self,\r\n        game: str = \"csgo\",\r\n        limit: int = 100,\r\n        offset: int = 0,\r\n        currency: str = \"USD\",\r\n        price_from: float | None = None,\r\n        price_to: float | None = None,\r\n        title: str | None = None,\r\n        sort: str = \"price\",\r\n        force_refresh: bool = False,\r\n        tree_filters: str | None = None,\r\n        cursor: str = \"\",\r\n    ) -> dict[str, Any]:\r\n        game_id = GAME_MAP.get(game.lower(), game)\r\n        params = {\r\n            \"gameId\": game_id,\r\n            \"limit\": limit,\r\n            \"offset\": offset,\r\n            \"currency\": currency,\r\n        }\r\n        if cursor:\r\n            params[\"cursor\"] = cursor\r\n        if price_from is not None:\r\n            params[\"priceFrom\"] = str(int(price_from * 100))\r\n        if price_to is not None:\r\n            params[\"priceTo\"] = str(int(price_to * 100))\r\n        if title:\r\n            params[\"title\"] = title\r\n        if sort:\r\n            params[\"orderBy\"] = sort\r\n        if tree_filters:\r\n            params[\"treeFilters\"] = tree_filters\r\n\r\n        return await self._request(\"GET\", \"/exchange/v1/market/items\", params=params, force_refresh=force_refresh)\r\n\r\n    async def get_suggested_price(self, item_name: str, game: str = \"csgo\") -> float | None:\r\n        response = await self.get_market_items(game=game, title=item_name, limit=1)\r\n        items = response.get(\"objects\", response.get(\"items\", []))\r\n        if not items:\r\n            return None\r\n        suggested = items[0].get(\"suggestedPrice\")\r\n        if isinstance(suggested, dict):\r\n            return float(suggested.get(\"amount\", 0)) / 100\r\n        return float(suggested) / 100 if suggested else None\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771157728574}}
{"type":"message","id":"dd500ae4","parentId":"9bce4cb0","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:15:39.604Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Defining Arbitrage Calculation**\n\nI'm currently focused on the arbitrage calculation. I've begun to define the key components. Specifically, I'm noting the `Ask Price`, which I'll get from the lowest listing using `get_market_items`. The next step is to get the `Bid Price`. I'll also use `get_market_items` for that. Then I'll work out the formula.\n\n\n**Clarifying Calculation Parameters**\n\nI'm now wrestling with the formula. It seems to imply a buy from the lowest listing, then sell to the highest bid. I need to clarify the fees and margin assumptions, because `(Ask Price * 0.93) - Bid Price` looks suspicious. I'll review the fee structure again, and consider if \"0.93\" represents a fee or discount.\n\n\n**Refining Price Acquisition Strategy**\n\nI've just been reviewing the code. I've noted that `get_market_items` provides the Ask (lowest selling price) side. However, I'm still trying to get the Bid (highest buying price). I have started examining trading.py, specifically looking for functions or API endpoints that will return the market's current bid. The prompt calculation suggests I'm focusing on spread and net.\n\n\n"},{"type":"text","text":"I will read `DMarket-Telegram-Bot-main/src/dmarket/api/trading.py` to find the method for retrieving the highest bid or target price for an item.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771157739489_611","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"DMarket-Telegram-Bot-main/src/dmarket/api/trading.py"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":12126,"output":648,"cacheRead":11369,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12774,"cost":{"input":0.024252,"output":0.007776,"cacheRead":0.0022738000000000003,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0343018}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771157728576}}
{"type":"message","id":"00bbb858","parentId":"dd500ae4","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:15:39.621Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771157739489_611","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"Trading operations for DMarket API.\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport logging\r\nfrom typing import Any\r\n\r\nfrom src.dmarket.circuit_breaker import circuit_breaker\r\n\r\nfrom .exceptions import CircuitBreakerError, InsufficientFundsError\r\n\r\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\r\n\r\nclass TradingMixin:\r\n    \"\"\"Methods for buying, selling and target management.\"\"\"\r\n\r\n    async def buy_item(self, item_id: str, price: float, game: str = \"csgo\") -> dict[str, Any]:\r\n        \"\"\"Buy item with balance safety check and circuit breaker.\"\"\"\r\n        \r\n        # 1. Circuit Breaker Check\r\n        if not circuit_breaker.can_trade():\r\n            msg = f\"Trading halted by Circuit Breaker: {circuit_breaker.trigger_reason}\"\r\n            logger.critical(msg)\r\n            raise CircuitBreakerError(msg)\r\n            \r\n        # 2. Safety Check: Get current balance\r\n        balance_info = await self.get_balance()\r\n        available = balance_info.available_balance if hasattr(balance_info, 'available_balance') else 0.0\r\n        \r\n        if price > available:\r\n            logger.error(f\"Purchase blocked: price ${price:.2f} > available ${available:.2f}\")\r\n            circuit_breaker.trip(f\"Insufficient funds: ${available:.2f} < ${price:.2f}\")\r\n            raise InsufficientFundsError(required=price, available=available)\r\n\r\n        if self.dry_run:\r\n            logger.info(f\"[DRY-RUN] Simulated buy: {item_id} @ ${price}\")\r\n            return {\"success\": True, \"dry_run\": True, \"message\": \"Simulated purchase\"}\r\n        \r\n        try:\r\n            data = {\r\n                \"itemId\": item_id,\r\n                \"price\": {\"amount\": int(price * 100), \"currency\": \"USD\"},\r\n                \"gameType\": game\r\n            }\r\n            # Execute trade\r\n            result = await self._request(\"POST\", \"/exchange/v1/market/items/buy\", data=data)\r\n            \r\n            # If successful, record success (resets consecutive losses)\r\n            if result.get(\"success\", False):\r\n                circuit_breaker.record_success()\r\n                \r\n            return result\r\n            \r\n        except Exception as e:\r\n            # Record potential API error or trade failure\r\n            logger.error(f\"Trade failed: {e}\")\r\n            circuit_breaker.record_api_error()\r\n            raise\r\n\r\n    async def sell_item(self, item_id: str, price: float) -> dict[str, Any]:\r\n        if self.dry_run:\r\n            logger.info(f\"[DRY-RUN] Simulated sell: {item_id} @ ${price}\")\r\n            return {\"success\": True, \"dry_run\": True}\r\n        \r\n        data = {\r\n            \"itemId\": item_id,\r\n            \"price\": {\"amount\": int(price * 100), \"currency\": \"USD\"}\r\n        }\r\n        return await self._request(\"POST\", \"/exchange/v1/user/inventory/sell\", data=data)\r\n\r\n    async def create_targets(self, game_id: str, targets: list[dict[str, Any]]) -> dict[str, Any]:\r\n        data = {\"GameID\": game_id, \"Targets\": targets}\r\n        return await self._request(\"POST\", \"/marketplace-api/v1/user-targets/create\", data=data)\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771157739620}}
