{"type":"message","id":"b0d485e1","parentId":"2f2c6f6b","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:16:19.322Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Reviewing the Evidence**\n\nI've been analyzing the output and found valuable confirmations. Specifically, `get_targets_by_title` is present within the `_api.py` files. Furthermore, `TargetsByTitleResponse` holds `orders` within the market models. This initial analysis is promising.\n\n\n**Confirming the Approach**\n\nI'm now certain of the API calls required. I'll need `get_market_items` and `get_targets_by_title`. I plan to begin with the three specified items: AK-47 Redline, AWP Asiimov, and Glock-18 Fade. The discrepancy between checking only three items and the request for \"5 items\" is noted. I am considering the need to expand my search beyond the initial three to fulfill that request, and am leaning towards pulling high volume items if the initial tests don't yield enough results.\n\n\n**Structuring the Implementation**\n\nNow I have a clearer approach. I will begin by constructing the core arbitrage logic, which will be encapsulated within a script. I'll initialize the API and iterate through the three specified items: AK-47 Redline, AWP Asiimov, and Glock-18 Fade. For each, I'll fetch the lowest ask and highest bid, calculate the net margin using the formula, and then implement the 3% constraint to filter results. I'm focusing on validating this core mechanism first before expanding the item list.\n\n\n**Finalizing Implementation Steps**\n\nI'm solidifying the plan. I'll focus on the arbitrage script, `hft_scan.py`, and then the subagent. My primary concern now is confirming the margin calculation: `((Ask * 0.93) - Bid) / Bid > 0.03`. To start, I'll calculate the ask and bid margins independently, focusing on the three example items. If that works, I'll expand to five total items, and introduce the steam price checks if the relevant API tools are found.\n\n\n**Developing the Subagent**\n\nI'm now focusing on creating `src/hft_scan_subagent.py`. I'll integrate the DMarket API calls, specifically `get_market_items` for asks and `get_targets_by_title` for bids. Then, I'll calculate the net margin using `((Ask * 0.93) - Bid) / Bid`. I'm starting with the initial three items and determining if I have the needed `steam` module to get the steam prices. I will look for any relevant code, and if there is no readily available implementation of the API, I will implement some kind of price approximation.\n\n\n"},{"type":"text","text":"I will search for `src/steam` or `steam_api.py` to identify the correct method for fetching Steam prices.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771157779317_618","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem -Recurse -Filter \"*steam*\""},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":45527,"output":1302,"cacheRead":14830,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46829,"cost":{"input":0.091054,"output":0.015624,"cacheRead":0.0029660000000000003,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.10964399999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771157761578}}
